Java 17 Features

Sealed Classes
Control class hierarchies for safer and clearer design.

Pattern Matching for switch (final)
Simplifies type and value-based switch statements.

Enhanced Pseudo-Random Number Generators
More flexible and high-quality random number generators.

Text Blocks (introduced earlier but widely used)
Multi-line string literals for cleaner code (Java 13+).

Records (introduced earlier but widely used)
Compact syntax for immutable data carriers (Java 16+).

Improved Null Handling (via Pattern Matching)
Better ways to check and cast objects safely.

Updated Stream API Enhancements (ongoing improvements)
Useful functional programming improvements.

Local-Variable Syntax for Lambda Parameters
More readable lambdas with var for parameters.